This paper is about task-oriented dialogue systems, which are commonly studied in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed method is based on reinforcement learning, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for training agents to interact with their environment. The paper also discusses the use of off-the-shelf models and fine-tuning optimization, which are common practices in machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SD). Finally, the paper presents experimental results that demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method, which is a common approach in neural engineering (cs.NE) for evaluating new models and algorithms.
